value.title: Where is Mike Pence?
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence hasn’t been seen publicly for three days. Pence, who heads the coronavirus task force and serves as president of the Senate, was not with the president in the briefing room Thursday night.

value.title: Biden on verge of winning U.S. presidency, leads in Pennsylvania, Georgia
value.excerpt: Democrat Joe Biden stood on the verge of winning the U.S. presidency on Friday, as he expanded his narrow leads over President Donald Trump in the battleground states of Pennsylvania and Georgia three days after polls closed.

value.title: Trump campaign hasn't provided evidence to back up claim of Wisconsin election 'irregularities'
value.excerpt: Trump and officials with his campaign have floated vague accusations with no evidence of election tampering in Wisconsin.

value.title: Trump Names Danly to Head FERC, Replacing Chatterjee
value.excerpt: Neil Chatterjee, who has backed policies in support of clean energy, is being replaced as head of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission by fellow commissioner James Danly.

value.title: Trump 'likely' to run again in 2024 if he loses: Mick Mulvaney
